--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Upstream data sources
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

`events.json` is assembled from several upstream sources. This project's
original contribution is the **curation and arrangement**: which issues
are part of which event, their depth-level classification (α/ε/Ω), the
role assignments (core / tie-in / context), the cross-references between
events, and the editorial notes. The underlying facts — issue titles,
numbers, publication years, cover URLs — come from:

  Comic Book Herald
  https://www.comicbookherald.com/
    Event reading orders scraped from public "reading guide" pages.
    The original selection of which issues belong to an event is CBH's
    editorial work; this project restructures that information and
    combines it with the sources below. When in doubt, cite CBH.

  Wikipedia
  https://en.wikipedia.org/
    Event summaries and title lists for crossovers CBH doesn't cover
    cleanly. Wikipedia content is licensed CC BY-SA 4.0. This project
    extracts only facts (titles, issue numbers, publication years) which
    are not subject to copyright (Feist Publications, Inc. v. Rural
    Telephone Service Co.); creative text is not redistributed.

  Marvel.com sitemap + bifrost GraphQL
  https://www.marvel.com/sitemap/ · bifrost.marvel.com
    Issue identifiers (marvelId, digitalId, DRN, slug) and cover URLs
    come from Marvel's public unauthenticated endpoints. Cover URLs in
    events.json point back to Marvel's own CDN; no images are
    redistributed.

  ComicVine API
  https://comicvine.gamespot.com/api/
    Cover URL fallback for series Marvel doesn't index on its sitemap.
    Fetched with a user-provided ComicVine API key. ComicVine's terms of
    service require attribution for any use of their data, which this
    NOTICE satisfies.

